<br>
Dear Diary,<br>
<br>
Something happened in the Guid Hall last night that may affect us all, <br>
It was evening, after dinner, and some of us were gathered around, just relaxing.  I remember sitting and trying to listen to Eryl playing on his lute as I was working on another bag for Masius, (he ripped a hole in his first one tracking something through a bramble thicket -that's what he said, anyhow. Personnaly, I think he just wants another one and didn't think I would give it to him.) Thorvan and Avaya were in the corner drinking, making lots of noise as always so it was hard to hear Eryl's song from where I was sitting.  A few of the others were there too, talking about the tower raid a couple days ago. It was like being among the family I lost when I was young.  I haven't been happier in a long time.  <br>
<br>
Anyhow, there we were when there was a big crash from Zarius's office. Everyone rushed down the hall all at once. There were too many people in the doorway for me to see, at first, but once everyone got straightened out..... It seems the noise was made by a couple pets that had gotten loose and had totally ripped the place apart. There were papers everywhere!  <br>
<br>
(Pets! they get into so much trouble if you don't watch them every second. Zarious really ought to ban them from the Hall.)<br>
<br>
Well, I'm still not sure who's pets were fighting in there but it's really odd because his office should have been locked and there should have been no way for them to get in.  They broke a couple vases and the statue Zarius keeps in the corner. The REALLY ugly one. He's going to be pretty upset when he finds out!<br>
<br>
Somehow,I ended up cleaning up the mess. I'm still not sure how THAT happened (I think my sister volunteered me)<br>
While I was picking up, and trying to put together some of the papers that had been chewed up, One of them caught my attention....I found as many pieces of it as I could and when I got it together, the message filled me with forboding... Here's what it said:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Zario -- of Blood Circle <br>
-------<br>
-------- regarding the --------- Guild Hall -- The --------<br>
--------------- act of Destruction ------------ most severe punishment we could devise. The threats and blood ------------ only the beginning. My name -----------.  ----- of Evil Inclination ------------traitor.  Again, ----------- you and your Guild ----------interfer---- raid. ----------------------- terms ---------- before tomorrow.<br>
<br>
Numamarin<br>
CoF </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Keep in mind, the paper was chewed up and hard to read, the scraps had coffee all over them.  But considering what happened last week, I thought it might be serious....<br>
So, I took the soggy scraps in to the main room and showed them to the officers. They seem to be taking the possible threat seriously.<br>
<br>
No one has seen Zarious since early this morning.<br>
I hope nothing has happened to him.<br>
<br>
                              Centuri<br>
                      Palidin of the 27th rank<br>
<br>
